                <h3>*Search the following keywords to match the cases:*</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Criminal Law</strong>: Involves cases related to criminal offenses. Relevant acts include the Indian Penal Code (IPC).</li>
                    <li><strong>Family Law</strong>: Deals with cases involving family matters, such as marriage and divorce. Relevant acts include the Hindu Marriage Act.</li>
                    <li><strong>Civil Rights</strong>: Encompasses cases protecting individuals' rights. Applicable acts include the Protection of Civil Rights Act.</li>
                    <li><strong>Property Law</strong>: Involves cases about property disputes and ownership. Relevant acts include the Transfer of Property Act.</li>
                    <li><strong>Corporate Fraud</strong>: Pertains to cases of corporate misconduct. Related acts include the Companies Act.</li>
                    <li><strong>Labour and Employment Law</strong>: Governs the rights and duties of workers and employers.</li>
                    <li><strong>Taxation Law</strong>: Deals with the levy and collection of taxes.</li>
                    <li><strong>Environmental Law</strong>: Focuses on the protection and preservation of the environment.</li>
                    <li><strong>Consumer Protection Law</strong>: Protects the rights of consumers in case of disputes related to goods, services, and contracts.</li>
                    <li><strong>Arbitration and Dispute Resolution</strong>: Deals with the settlement of disputes outside of courts.</li>
                    <li><strong>Immigration Law</strong>: Deals with the entry, stay, and exit of individuals in a country.</li>
                    <li><strong>Banking and Finance Law</strong>: Regulates the banking and financial industry.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

